---
source: crates/carta/tests/golden_e2e.rs
expression: output
---
A plain © sign decodes in running text.

Monospace \texttt{\&} decodes, as do a \textsubscript{©} subscript, a
\textsuperscript{®} superscript, and a \st{©} deletion.

A link label \href{start}{\&copy;} keeps the entity literal, and so does
a \&copy; span and a verbatim block:

\begin{verbatim}
&copy;
\end{verbatim}
